<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-24-1026 </DOCNO><TEXT>Since the Sunshine Project of Japan started in 1974, efficient researchand development have been in progress under close industrial-academic-governmentcooperation for the study of new energy technologies such as solar energy,geothermal engergy, liquefaction and gasification of coal, hydrogen energy,etc. It is now in the stage of research using full-scale experimentalplants for the major research and development projects, based on theresult of the fundamental study. The project is planned to be promotedwith priority given to the research and development of coal liquefactionand gasification technology, solar engery power generation technology,investigation and application technology of geothermal resources, etc.The plan is to promote the development of technologies, relating to theabove technological fields, for industrial solar system, power generationutilizing hot water, power generation utilizing hot dry rock, hydrogenproduction utilizing coal, etc. (2 figs, 3 tabs)</TEXT></DOC>